r modern development teams.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}], \"version\": \"2.30.7\"}','2024-12-02 13:21:16.483702','Introduction to Agile: Principles and Practices','2024-12-02 13:21:16.483729',9,4),(22,'{\"time\": 1733120503776, \"blocks\": [{\"id\": \"i1gb5Dpm7I\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Introduction\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"kipk1BcvYk\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Scrum is a widely-used Agile framework that organizes work into time-boxed iterations called sprints. It emphasizes team roles, ceremonies, and artifacts for effective project management.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}, {\"id\": \"4YFFvuiRvT\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Key Roles in Scrum\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"0jrqRnvcFu\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Product Owner: Manages the product backlog and defines priorities.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Scrum Master: Facilitates the process and removes impediments.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Development Team: Delivers the product increment during the sprint.\"}], \"style\": \"ordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"Bf5_o1iQM8\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Key Ceremonies in Scrum\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"xJrVubKu0t\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Sprint Planning: Define sprint goals and backlog items.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Daily Stand-Up: Quick status updates to align the team.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Sprint Review: Showcase the completed work to stakeholders.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Retrospective: Reflect on the sprint and identify areas for improvement.\"}], \"style\": \"unordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"wDVNLIeW7A\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Benefits of Scrum\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"RaT8b2ucsf\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Clear accountability and roles.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Regular feedback loops.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Continuous improvement through retrospectives.\"}], \"style\": \"unordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"CdbDWpH1pg\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Conclusion\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"_knirzptzO\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Scrum helps teams stay focused, aligned, and productive. Understanding its roles and ceremonies is crucial for implementing Agile effectively.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}], \"version\": \"2.30.7\"}','2024-12-02 13:21:43.813361','Scrum Framework: Key Roles and Ceremonies','2024-12-02 13:21:43.813394',9,4),(23,'{\"time\": 1733120531531, \"blocks\": [{\"id\": \"YYLgqzV-4r\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Introduction\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"Y9GqTvYhus\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Kanban is an Agile methodology that emphasizes visualizing workflows and optimizing task flow to improve efficiency.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}, {\"id\": \"V0oTttwtIu\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Key Concepts in Kanban\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"4wgJlKuJIs\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Visual Workflow: Use boards with columns to represent task stages.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Work in Progress (WIP) Limits: Restrict ongoing tasks to prevent overload.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Continuous Delivery: Deliver features as soon as they are ready.\"}], \"style\": \"ordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"sYG6VBb4ZA\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Setting Up a Kanban Board\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"-tVw3zfoGH\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Create columns (e.g., To Do, In Progress, Done).\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Add 