\"unordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"RJhiD0tZLy\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Conclusion\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"9-vtdvw8BT\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Column-family stores provide the flexibility and scalability required for big data applications, making them a key component of modern data architectures.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}], \"version\": \"2.30.7\"}','2024-12-02 14:13:16.221930','Column-Family Stores: Handling Wide Data','2024-12-02 14:13:16.221975',24,7),(65,'{\"time\": 1733123800608, \"blocks\": [{\"id\": \"U5n_DrNb2c\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Introduction\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"aKOhZO7G8i\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Processes and threads are fundamental concepts in operating systems. A process is an executing instance of a program, while threads are smaller units of execution within a process.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}, {\"id\": \"C8PFGE3Z1B\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Key Concepts\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"7TztsxPjz9\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {\"counterType\": \"numeric\"}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Processes:<ul><li data-empty=\\\"false\\\">Independent entities with their own memory and resources.</li><li data-empty=\\\"false\\\">Can communicate via inter-process communication (IPC).</li></ul>\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Threads:<ul><li data-empty=\\\"false\\\">Share the process\'s memory and resources.</li><li data-empty=\\\"false\\\">Lightweight compared to processes.</li></ul>\"}], \"style\": \"ordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"KIisQbB6n3\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"States of a Process\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"U7ZJDlYJlR\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"New: Process is being created.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Ready: Process is ready to execute.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Running: Process is being executed.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Waiting: Process is waiting for a resource.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Terminated: Process has finished execution.\"}], \"style\": \"unordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"IM_C7eGoC6\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Applications\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"TEVGQL2qG1\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Multitasking environments.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Web servers managing multiple requests.\"}], \"style\": \"unordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"JHXRkINJJE\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Conclusion\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"gCxcqB6AQD\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Understanding processes and threads is crucial for designing efficient systems that can manage concurrent tasks seamlessly.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}], \"version\": \"2.30.7\"}','2024-12-02 14:16:08.408208','Introduction to Processes and Threads','2024-12-02 14:16:40.654677',25,8),(66,'{\"time\": 1733123839079, \"blocks\": [{\"id\": \"7TxqjwzIZg\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Introduction\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"zLCGNTd_vu\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"CPU scheduling determines the order in which processes execute on the CPU. It aims to maximize resource utilization and ensure fairness among processes.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}, {\"id\": \"JbCaMDPUy-\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Scheduling Algorithms\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"g2cY9Z5lkO\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"First-Come, First-Served (FCFS): Processes are executed in the order they arrive.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Shortest Job Next (SJN): Prioritizes processes with the shortest burst time.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Round Robin (RR): Allocates fixed time slices to each process.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Priority Scheduling: Executes processes based on assigned priorities.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Multilevel Queue Scheduling: Divides processes into categories and schedules them separately.\"}], \"style\": \"ordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"i11u6YQkpE\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Performance Metrics\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"MCoT4QL5kV\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Throughput: Number of processes completed per unit time.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Turnaround Time: Total time taken for process execution.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Waiting Time: Time spent waiting in the ready queue.\"}], \"style\": \"unordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"rIwBocTlgD\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Conclusion\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"n2m3Owz9pH\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"CPU scheduling algorithms balance efficiency and fairness, ensuring optimal resource allocation in multitasking systems.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}], \"version\": \"2.30.7\"}','2024-12-02 14:17:19.115406','CPU Scheduling: Optimizing Process Execution','2024-12-02 14:17:19.115450',25,8),(67,'{\"time\": 1733123854459, \"blocks\": [{\"id\": \"38jyh0QfCK\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Introduction\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"JXKRV3PPv4\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Inter-Process Communication (IPC) allows processes to exchange information and coordinate their actions. It is essential for systems with multiple processes working collaboratively.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}, {\"id\": \"Hc0gARIIve\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Common IPC Mechanisms\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"AB1-xMb6oY\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Message Passing: Processes communicate by sending and receiving messages.<ul><li data-empty=\\\"false\\\">Examples: Pipes, message queues.</li></ul>\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Shared Memory: Processes access a common memory space for data exchange.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Semaphores: Synchronize access to shared resources to prevent conflicts.\"}], \"style\": \"ordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"UzyKPXE4Hn\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Examples\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"8etILxdAAR\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Client-server models for communication.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Multi-threaded applications requiring data synchronization.\"}], \"style\": \"unordered\"}, \"type\": \"list\"}, {\"id\": \"Hzk3pXwOeg\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Conclusion\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"y8czB4b2Ul\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"IPC mechanisms enable efficient collaboration between processes, ensuring smooth execution in distributed systems.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}], \"version\": \"2.30.7\"}','2024-12-02 14:17:34.491395','Inter-Process Communication (IPC): Enabling Process Collaboration','2024-12-02 14:17:34.491428',25,8),(68,'{\"time\": 1733123872192, \"blocks\": [{\"id\": \"B_ef4HJGU_\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Introduction\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"Riv97jBBk3\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"A deadlock occurs when a set of processes is unable to proceed because each process is waiting for a resource held by another. It is a critical issue in process management.\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph\"}, {\"id\": \"KDpR_XNhTa\", \"data\": {\"text\": \"Conditions for Deadlock\", \"level\": 3}, \"type\": \"header\"}, {\"id\": \"N4R5gz9xA_\", \"data\": {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [{\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Mutual Exclusion: Resources cannot be shared.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"items\": [], \"content\": \"Hold and Wait: Processes hold resources while waiting for others.\"}, {\"meta\": {}, \"i